article.description: Tori Jankoska scored a career-high 30 points, including five 3-pointers, to lead No. 20 Michigan State to a 103-63 win over Cincinnati in the Jankanoo Jam on Friday.
article.headline: No. 20 Michigan State women cruise past Cincinnati 103-63
article.linkText: No. 20 Michigan State women cruise past Cincinnati 103-63
article.story:
FREEPORT, Bahamas --  Tori Jankoska scored a career-high 30 points, including five 3-pointers, to lead No. 20 Michigan State to a 103-63 win over Cincinnati in the Jankanoo Jam on Friday.

Aerial Powers added 20 points to go with six rebounds and Branndais Agee had 10 points for Michigan State (4-0), which pierced the triple-digit scoring mark for the first time since 2013. The Wolverines hit 59 percent of their 65 shots from the field and controlled the boards 43-22.

Taking a 49-30 advantage into the break, Michigan State broke it open with a big third quarter, outscoring Cincinnati 35-16 to take a commanding lead it held the rest of the way.

Jasmine Whitfield led Cincinnati (3-2) with 14 points and Bianca Quisenberry added 10. The Bearcats were held to 40 percent shooting from the field and just three of 11 from long range.
